      "message": "Thanks for clarify the expected behavior.\n\nTo me, the code i sent you does not look like it would have a bug.\n\nThe server is only default constructing an interface (which it probably should not)\nbut it\u0027s looking quite harmless.\n\nAnd i don\u0027t see people testing for remote peers to suddenly disconnect.\n\nWe can default construct to `/` (my preference) or `/invalid` to prevent these issues.\n\nIf we choose `/invalid` then you get to keep the pieces,\n\nif we go with `/` then i will fix up the resulting problems (if there are any) for a few months.\n\nAlternatively we can also accept this bug or sprinkle a few more try-catch into the code.",
